# Jekyll Blog Development

This is a Jekyll blog using GitHub Pages with the minimal theme.

## Development Workflow
- Use `make serve` to start local development server with live reload
- Use `make build` for production builds
- Use `make install` to install/update dependencies
- Use `make clean` to clean build artifacts

## Blog Structure
- `_posts/`: Blog post markdown files with YYYY-MM-DD-title.md format
- `_layouts/`: HTML template files (home.html, post.html, post_no_sidebar.html)
- `_config.yml`: Jekyll configuration
- `assets/`: Static files (CSS, images)
- `index.html`: Homepage template

## Content Guidelines
- Blog posts should have proper front matter with title, date, and layout
- Images should be stored in `assets/images/` with organized subdirectories
- Use kramdown markdown with GFM syntax
- Posts automatically get permalink format: /:year/:month/:day/:title/

## Theme & Styling
- Using remote theme: pages-themes/minimal@v0.2.0
- Custom styles in `assets/css/style.css`  
- Responsive design with modern, clean layout

